cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for generating building footprints from satellite images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an improved GAN architecture, which falls under the category of generative models and deep learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with urban modeling, which falls under the category of graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for automatic generation of building footprints, which can be applied to robotics and automation, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
